USA: Fire in Philadelphia home for disabled kills four.Fire in Philadelphia home for disabled kills four.- Four people died in an overnight fire at a group residence for the disabled in Philadelphia's Chester County suburb of Exton, police said Tuesday.The dead included a female counsellor and three elderly male residents, two of whom needed wheelchairs. They were found inside the one-story house after firemen extinguished the fierce flames. A neighbour alerted by his barking dog sounded the alarm at 2:20 a.m. EDT (0620 GMT).West Whiteland Township police withheld the identity of the dead while relatives were being notified.